HEADWORD: Trisect
<hw>Tri*sect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Trisected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Trisecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>tri-</ets> + L.
<ets>sectus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>secare</ets> to cut. See
<er>Section</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut or divide into three
parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>To cut or divide into three equal
parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trisected</ent>⟦br⟧
